{u'speaker_state': u'NY', u'speaker_raw': u'mr. ackerman', u'speaker_first': u'Gary', u'congress': 110, u'title': u'TRIBUTE TO MARTIN RICHARDS IN HONOR OF HIS BIRTHDAY', u'origin_url': u'http://origin.www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/CREC-2007-03-09/html/CREC-2007-03-09-pt1-PgE515-2.htm', u'number': 41, u'id': u'CREC-2007-03-09-pt1-PgE515-2.chunk0', u'volume': 153, u'chamber': u'Extensions', u'session': 1, u'speaker_last': u'Ackerman', u'pages': u'E515', u'speaker_party': u'D', u'date': u'2007-03-09', u'bills': None, u'bioguide_id': u'A000022', u'order': 0, u'speaking': [u'Madam Speaker, I rise before this historic chamber of the House of Representatives to call to the attention of this Congress the profound achievements of Martin Richards as we honor him on his birthday this March 11.', u"Many here and throughout our nation know of Mr. Richards through his extraordinary accomplishments as a theatrical and movie producer, having won our nations' highest awards including an Oscar for best picture, numerous Tony Awards for his Broadway productions, and a Pulitzer Prize.", u"Martin Richards has also blessed the lives of so many New Yorkers through his vision and leadership on behalf of so many seeking hope and opportunity. In 1997, Mayor Giuliani appointed him to a six-year term as a member of The Trust for Cultural Resources of the City of New York. He was also a member of the Mayor's Advisory Council for Theatre.", u"Mr. Richards served on the President's Council for the Gay Men's Health Crisis, and is on the Board of Directors of Broadway Cares/Equity Fights AIDS. In 1994, in memory of his wife, he established the Mary Lea Johnson Richards Institute at New York University Medical Center for organ transplantation and research, and in 1995, also in memory of his wife, he co-founded the Children's Advocacy Center of Manhattan, New York City's only non-profit center for abused children. For the past eight years he has produced the annual Red Ball, one of New York's premiere charitable events, which benefits both the Institute and the Advocacy Center.", u"Martin Richards' life is a living example of the expression that one man can truly make a difference. This boy from the Bronx has brought dreams and joy to audiences throughout the world though his work. By celebrating Martin Richards' birthday, we take pride in the ideals that define the greatness of New York City.", u'Madam Speaker, I ask all my colleagues in the House of Representatives to join me now in honoring Martin Richards for bringing joy and hope to the people of New York City and the entire nation.'], u'capitolwords_url': u'http://capitolwords.org/date/2007/03/09/E515-2_tribute-to-martin-richards-in-honor-of-his-birthda/'}